{"name": "rel", "metadata": {"name": "rel", "version": "0.4.9.19", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 5 - Production/Stable", "Environment :: Console", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python", "Topic :: Software Development :: Libraries :: Python Modules"], "home_page": null, "license": "MIT License", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "Registered Event Listener. Provides standard (pyevent) interface and functionality without external dependencies", "upload_time": 1715224505}, "documentation": ["Registered Event Listener (rel) is a cross-platform asynchronous event dispatcher primarily designed for network applications. Select your preferred event notification methods with initialize([methods in order of preference]). If initialize(...) is not called, methods are tried in the default order: epoll, kqueue, poll, select, pyevent. Code and docs live on github: https://github.com/bubbleboy14/registeredeventlistener\n"], "modules": [{"name": "rel.errors", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "rel.errors.AbortBranch", "bases": ["Exception"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}], "exports": []}, {"name": "rel.tools", "documentation": ["This module contains a single tool (Timer) and a\nCLI wrapper (timerCLI()).\n\n### Timer\nTimer's start() function contains basic usage examples\nof the timeout(), signal(), and dispatch() functions:\n\n    def start(self):\n        self.count = 0\n        notice(\"starting countdown to %s\"%(self.goal,))\n        rel.timeout(1, self.update)\n        rel.signal(2, self.stop)\n        rel.dispatch()\n\nSimilarly, Timer.stop() triggers rel.abort().\n\n### timerCLI\nThis function contains an example of rel initialization,\nwhich is optional, but may be used to specify particular\nsettings:\n\n    if options.verbose:\n        rel.initialize(options=[\"verbose\"])\n\n### usage\n\n    rtimer [seconds] [minutes] [hours] [update_increment]\n\nAll arguments default to zero. So:\n\n    rtimer 15 30 2 60\n\nmeans run for 15 seconds, 30 minutes, and 2 hours, printing\na notice every 60 seconds.\n\n    rtimer 0 5\n\nmeans run for 5 minutes, printing no incremental updates.\n\nThe -s, -m, -r, and -i flags may also be used to indicate\nseconds, minutes, hours, and increment, and if any flag is\nspecified, update_increment defaults to 1 (instead of 0).\n\nWhen the time runs out, a sound will play on two conditions:\nthere is a readable file at the specified path (configurable\nvia the -p flag, with default: ~/.rtimer/),\nand mplayer is installed."], "functions": [{"name": "rel.tools.notice", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "*lines", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["## helper functions"]}, {"name": "rel.tools.exit", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "rel.tools.error", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "msg", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "*lines", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "rel.tools.timerCLI", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": ["## functions for interpreting command-line instructions", "rtimer"]}], "variables": [{"name": "rel.tools.RT_MEDIA", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "rel.tools.RT_USAGE", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "rel.tools.Timer", "bases": ["object"], "methods": [{"name": "rel.tools.Timer.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "s", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "m", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "h", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "interval", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "mediapath", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "rel.tools.Timer.start", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "rel.tools.Timer.stop", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "rel.tools.Timer.update", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "rel.tools.Timer.alarm", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}], "exports": []}, {"name": "rel.test", "documentation": ["REL Test Suite - regular unittest compatible suite\nSubmitted by Chris Clark on 10/12/2011. Thanks, Chris!\n\nOriginal code here:\nhttp://code.google.com/r/clach04-pyeventtestfixes/source/browse/test.py\n\nSample usage:\n\n    rel est.py\n    rel est.py -v\n    rel est.py -v EventTest.test_exception EventTest.test_timeout\n    ... etc."], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "rel.test.unittest2", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "rel.test.possible_build_dir", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "rel.test.EventTest", "bases": ["unittest.TestCase"], "methods": [{"name": "rel.test.EventTest.skip", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "reason", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Skip current test because of `reason`.\n\nNOTE currently expects unittest2, and defaults to \"pass\"\nif not available.\n\nunittest2 does NOT work under Python 2.2.\nCould potentially use nose or py.test which has (previously)\nsupported Python 2.2\n  * nose\n    http://python-nose.googlecode.com/svn/wiki/NoseWithPython2_2.wiki\n  * py.test\n    http://codespeak.net/pipermail/py-dev/2005-February/000203.html"]}, {"name": "rel.test.EventTest.setUp", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "rel.test.EventTest.test_timeout", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "rel.test.EventTest.test_timeout2", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "rel.test.EventTest.test_signal", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "rel.test.EventTest.test_signal2", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "rel.test.EventTest.test_read", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "rel.test.EventTest.test_read2", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "rel.test.EventTest.test_exception", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "rel.test.EventTest.test_abort", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "rel.test.EventTest.test_callback_exception", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "rel.test.EventTest.test_thread", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}], "exports": []}, {"name": "rel.rel", "documentation": ["R.E.L.\nRegisted Event Listener is a pure-python implementation of [pyevent](https://github.com/jaraco/pyevent),\nwhich is a wrapper around [libevent](http://monkey.org/~provos/libevent/), providing an identical interface\nwithout the need to compile C code, and without breaking the GIL / threading.\n\n### basic functions:\n    read(socket, callback, *args)\n    write(socket, callback, *args)\n    timeout(delay, callback, *args)\n    signal(sig, callback, *args)\n    event(callback,arg=None,evtype=0,handle=None)\n    dispatch()\n    loop()\n    abort()\n    abort_branch() (non-pyevent only)\n    thread()\n    init()\n\n### registrars\nrel will use the fastest registrar available on your system:\n\n    supported_methods = ['epoll','kqueue','poll','select','pyevent']\n\nThe supported_methods[] registrar priority list, as well as other\nsettings, can be altered using the (optional) initialize() function:\n\n### initialize(methods=supported_methods,options=()) - possible options:\n    'verbose' - prints out certain events\n    'report' - prints status of non-pyevent registrar every 5 seconds\n    'strict' - ONLY try specified methods\n    'threaded' - enable GIL hack -- pyevent only!\n\n### override()\nThis override function can be used to seamlessly swap rel into\na pyevent application."], "functions": [{"name": "rel.rel.override", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "rel.rel.log", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "text", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "rel.rel.__report", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "rel.rel.check_init", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "rel.rel.get_registrar", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "method", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "rel.rel.set_verbose", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "isverb", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "rel.rel.initialize", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "methods", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "options", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["initialize(methods=['epoll','kqueue','poll','select','pyevent'],options=[])\npossible options:\n    'verbose' - prints out certain events\n    'report' - prints status of non-pyevent registrar every 5 seconds\n    'strict' - ONLY try specified methods\n    'threaded' - enable GIL hack -- pyevent only!"]}, {"name": "rel.rel.safe_read", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "rel.rel.read", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "sock", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "cb", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "*args", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "rel.rel.write", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "sock", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "cb", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "*args", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "rel.rel.error", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "sock", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "cb", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "*args", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "rel.rel.timeout", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "delay", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "cb", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "*args", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "rel.rel.signal", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "sig", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "callback", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "*args", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name"